data.chText: （尤指割了庄稼的）一长条田地
data.enText: a long strip of land, especially one on which the plants or crops have been cut

data.chText: 联合收割机把庄稼绕田边割了一长条。
data.enText: The combine had cut a swathe around the edge of the field.

data.chText: 开发建设影响了乡村广大地区。
data.enText: Development has affected vast swathes of our countryside.
a large strip or area of sth
The mountains rose above a swathe of thick cloud.

data.chText: 把（某地的一片）夷为平地；使…大部分遭受破坏
data.enText: to pass through a particular area destroying a large part of it
to wrap or cover sb/sth in sth

data.chText: 他裹着绷带，躺在医院的病床上。
data.enText: He was lying on the hospital bed, swathed in bandages.

means: (尤指割了庄稼的)一长条田地

data.chText: 把（某地的一片）夷为平地；使…大部分遭受破坏
data.enText: to pass through a particular area destroying a large part of it

value.boxr_value: The noun is also spelled swath.

value.def: A swathe of land is a long strip of land.

example.ex: On May 1st the army took over another swathe of territory...
example.tran: 军队在5月1号又接管了另一长条领土。

example.ex: Year by year great swathes of this small nation's countryside disappear.
example.tran: 年复一年,这个小国家的乡村面积正在一片片地大量消失。

value.def: A swathe of cloth is a long strip of cloth, especially one that is wrapped around someone or something.
value.tran: 一长条(尤指用来包裹某人或某物的布料)

value.def: To swathe someone or something in cloth means to wrap them in it completely.

example.ex: She swathed her enormous body in thin black fabrics...
example.tran: 她用薄薄的黑色织物裹住了自己硕大的身躯。

example.ex: His head was swathed in bandages made from a torn sheet.
example.tran: 他的头上缠满了一层层用床单撕成的绷带。

value.def: If a person or thing cuts a swathe through something, they pass through it causing great destruction or change.

example.ex: The storm cut a swathe through southern England...
example.tran: 风暴重创了英格兰南部。

example.ex: Keegan's team have been cutting an irresistible swathe through the first division.
example.tran: 基冈的球队在甲级赛中所向披靡。

value.tran: 使遭到严重破坏;使发生巨变
